What you need to know:  The NLCÂ has warned that critical services such as digitisation of land records risk being affected if it does not get Sh1.3 billion in the supplementary budget.NLC chairman Gershom Otachi told the National Assembly committee on lands that the commission will be forced to scale down a number of core services due to massive budget cuts.He told MPs that NLC had already advertised for a tender to upgrade its ICT infrastructure in order to link its headquarters in Nairobi with their county ones to reduce physical visits, but the activity is now in jeopardy.